scretion to the formal. In this liminal space, this book considers how sex work is policed and how it should be policed. Challenging discourses about sexuality and gender that inform its regulation, Thusi exposes the limitations of dominant feminist arguments regarding the legal treatment of sex work. This in-depth, historically informed ethnography illustrates the tension between enforcing a country's laws and protecting citizens' human rights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHuman rightszSouth Africa. 0aLaw enforcementzSouth AfricazJohannesburg. 0aProstitutionxLaw and legislationzSouth Africa. 0aProstitutionzSouth AfricazJohannesburg. 0aSex workersxLegal status, laws, etczSouth Africa. 0aSex workersxLegal status, laws, etc.zSouth Africa. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh  a(de)criminalization.  acriminal law.  aethnography.  afeminism.  agender.  ahuman rights.  apolicing of sex.  aprostitution.  asex work.  asexuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishz978311075409408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021z9783110753868oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362975240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503629752423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503629752/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075409-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2021